---
description: Enforces American English as the standard language for all source code
alwaysApply: true
---

# Goal
All source code must be in American English.

## Scope
Applies to:
- Variables
- Functions
- Classes
- Files and folders
- Tests
- Technical comments

## Do
- Use standard computing terminology.
- Reuse naming patterns already established in the repository.
- Keep code locale-agnostic (dates, numbers, timezones, formatting).

## Do not
- Mix languages in identifiers.
- Use accents or special characters in identifiers.
- Translate technical concepts literally when it degrades meaning.

## Exceptions
Portuguese terms are allowed only for official Brazilian legal or regulatory concepts.
When used:
- Keep the term fully in Portuguese.
- Isolate it in domain-specific modules.
- Add an English comment explaining the term and why it cannot be translated.

